<Verbatim PAsource="" >CHANGING Rooms </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >star Liz </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >Wagstaff </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >conned pals </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >and colleagues out of </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >nearly £60,000 </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >by pretending she had cancer,</Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" > a court heard </New>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >yesterday.</Rewrite>


<Verbatim PAsource="" >Wagstaff, 38, </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >is </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >said to have </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >told </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >14 </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >people that she needed cash for medical treatment because she was terminally ill.</Rewrite>


<New PAsource="" >BBC co-hosts Anna Ryder-Richardson and Mike Jewitt each gave her £500 while the wife of anchorman Lawrence Llewellyn-Bowen handed over £3,500, </New>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >Inner London Crown Court </Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" >heard.</New>


<New PAsource="" >Other alleged victims include her ex-lover Mark Thurgood, who is said to have given her £12,000.

The interior designer - who made five appearances in the hit makeover show - </New>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >faces 19 charges </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >of obtaining a </Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" >total of £55,650 </New>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >by deception</Verbatim> 
<Verbatim PAsource="" >between July 1998 and last August.</Verbatim>


<Verbatim PAsource="" >Wagstaff of Stevenage, </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >Herts, denies the charges.

She was bailed until </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >April 25.</Verbatim>



